The immediate past Minister of State for Agriculture and Rural Development and APC gubernatorial aspirant in Bayelsa State, Senator Heineken Lokpobiri, has congratulated Chief Timipre Sylva over his ministerial nomination. The senator’s Special Assistant on Media, Mr George Oji, in a statement in Yenagoa, yesterday, said Lokpobiri had shortly after the announcement at the floor of the Senate sent a personal message to Sylva congratulating him on his appointment. He described Sylva’s appointment as well deserved, adding that this was the type of development Bayelsa APC needed to wrest power from the ruling Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the state come November 16. Lokpobiri, the only APC gubernatorial aspirant in the state so far, noted that APC was “very optimistic that the November 16, 2019 gubernatorial election in the state will go the way of the party.” Bayelsa: Suspense, anxiety as aspirants scramble for APC gov’ship ticket When things fell apart in Bayelsa APC Ex minister, Lokpobiri declares for Bayelsa governorship Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin